value.value: 睡眠行動の異常
any anomaly in the actions, reactions, or performance of an organism during a periodic, readily reversible state of reduced awareness and metabolic activity
神経内膜浮腫
an excessive accumulation of serous fluid in the interstitial connective tissue of a peripheral nerve
神経内膜液圧の異常
measureable anomalies in the fluid of the ganglia and peripheral nerves that lie outside the brain and spinal cord which may interfere with normal nerve physiology
神経内膜液圧上昇
a measureable increase of serous fluid in the interstitial connective tissue of a peripheral nerve which may interefere with normal nerve physiology
完全な致死
all individuals of a given genotype in a population die before the end of the normal lifespan but time(s) of death are unspecified
血管平滑筋の発生異常
anomaly in the process of forming the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue of the blood vessels
腎円柱

any of the various casts formed from gelled protein precipitated in the distal convoluted tubules and collecting ducts of nephrons and molded to the tubular or duct lumen which dislodge and pass into the urine; types named for their constituent material include acellular casts (e.g. granular, hyaline, waxy, or fatty casts) and cellular casts (e.g. red or white blood cell casts)
腎盂腎炎

a diffuse pyogenic infection of the pelvis and parenchyma of the kidney; an ascending urinary tract infection that has reached the pyelum or pelvis of the kidney usually resulting from noncontagious bacterial infection of the bladder
腎盂炎
acute inflammation of the pelvis of the kidney, caused by bacterial infection
尿細管間質性腎炎

diffuse or local inflammation and edema of the interstitial tissue of the kidney, including the renal tubules; usually secondary to drug sensitization, systemic infection, graft rejection, or autoimmune disease
後台形核の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the loose collection of neurons that reside in the rostral medulla close to the medullary surface, ventral and immediately caudal of nVII, that are crucial for CO2 sensing in the brain
腎発生帯域の欠如

absence of the region found at the periphery of the developing metanephros within which the metanephric mesenchyme aggregates around the tips of the ureteric tree to form the nephrons;in rodents including mice, this region normally persists for a few days postnatally, although it is lost in humans by 36 weeks of gestation
腎尿細管肥大
increase in the bulk size of the loop of Henle, the proximal convoluted tubule or the distal convoluted tubule, due to cell enlargement

value.value: 腎糸球体基底膜の厚さ増加

value.value: increased width of the layer of extracellular matrix that lies between the endothelium of the glomerular capillaries and the podocytes of the inner or visceral layer of the Bowman capsule
異所性精巣、精巣転位
one or both of the testes located outside the normal pathway of descent into the scrotum
生殖腺隆起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the elevation of thickened mesothelium and underlying mesenchyme found on the ventromedial border of the embryonic mesonephros in which the primordial germ cells become embedded, establishing it as the primordium of the testis or ovary
生殖腺隆起形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the gonadal ridge, typically resulting in decreased size
無色の尿
absence of the usual straw-coloration of the urine
赤尿
passage of red colored urine
アルドステロン値異常
anomaly in the concentration of the hormone that is secreted by the adrenal cortex and regulates sodium conservation and potassium secretion in the distal renal tubule
精巣間質の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the delicate connective tissue stroma that separates the seminiferous tubules and contains clusters of endocrine Leydig cells which secrete testosterone
腎輸送の異常
any anomaly of the directed movement of substances through the kidney
白血球尿
presence of white blood cells in the urine
赤血球尿症
presence of red blood cells in the urine

definition.value: Hematuria (presence of blood in the urine), erythrocyturia (presence of red blood cells in the urine),and erythruria (passage of red urine,) are often used interchangeably.

value.value: 膿尿
presence of pus in the urine when voided; a sign of inflammation often related to urinary tract infection
円柱尿
presence of renal cylinders or casts in the urine
腎髄質萎縮

acquired diminution of the size of the inner portion of the kidney consisting of the renal pyramids, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
腎皮質萎縮

acquired diminution of the size of the outer portion of the kidney located between the renal capsule and the renal medulla, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
尿中尿酸濃度低下

abnormally low amount in the urine of the final oxidation product of purine catabolism in humans and primates, but which in rodents and most other mammals is normally is further oxidized by uricase to allantoin that is excreted in the urine
腎間質の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the kidney region located between the nephrons, ureteric epithelia (ureteric tips, trunk and collecting duct system) and renal vasculature, and composed of renal support cells, including fibroblasts and macrophages, and mesenchymal stroma or interstitial cells; the renal vasculature lies within the renal interstitium but is not a part of it; various conditions can lead to scarring (fibrosis) and congestion of this area, which can cause kidney dysfunction and failure
子宮平滑筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the smooth muscle tissue surrounding the epithelium of the ureter
メサンギウム細胞過形成
increased number of the phagocytic cells in the capillary tuft of the renal glomerulus, interposed between endothelial cells and the basement membrane in the central or stalk region of the tuft
メサンギウム細胞形成不全
decreased number of the phagocytic cells in the capillary tuft of the renal glomerulus, interposed between endothelial cells and the basement membrane in the central or stalk region of the tuft
メサンギウム細胞の欠如
absence of the phagocytic cells in the capillary tuft of the renal glomerulus, normally interposed between endothelial cells and the basement membrane in the central or stalk region of the tuft
メサンギウム融解

an injurious glomerular process that affects primarily the mesangium, starting with loosening and detachment of its matrix and progressing to dissolution/attenuation with degeneration of mesangial cells; mesangial cells may show only edema and vacuolization, or may undergo severe degeneration and necrosis
尿流量の増加
increased volume of urine produced in a specified period of time
尿流量の減少
reduced volume of urine produced in a specified period of time
糸球体毛細血管うっ血
obstruction of the normal flux of blood within the renal glomerular capillaries
尿中マグネシウム濃度異常
any change in the amount of magnesium in the urine
尿中マグネシウム濃度上昇
higher than normal amount of magnesium in the urine
尿中マグネシウム濃度低下
lower than normal amount of magnesium in the urine
糸球体出血
bleeding in the renal glomerulus
腎髄質欠如
failure of the inner portion of the kidney, normally consisting of the renal pyramids, to form
腎細胞増殖異常
anomaly in the ability of any kidney cell population to undergo expansion by cell division
腎細胞増殖増加
increase in the expansion rate of any kidney cell population by cell division
腎細胞増殖低下
decrease in the expansion rate of any kidney cell population by cell division
腎ナトリウムイオン輸送異常
any anomaly in the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) by the kidney
腎の水輸送異常
any anomaly in the directed movement of water (H2O) by the kidney
腎の水恒常性異常
any anomaly in the kidney processes involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of water in the body
腎タンパク質再吸収異常
any anomaly in the process in which proteins are taken up from the collecting ducts and proximal and distal loops of the nephron
